Vale Plans to Start Coal Mining at Moatize in Mozambique

-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 
2011-05-05T02:53:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/vale-plans-to-start-coal-mining-at-moatize-in-mozambique.html
Vale SA (VALE3) , the world’s largest iron–ore
producer, will begin mining coal at its Moatize mine on Sunday,
the  Rio de Janeiro  based company said in an e-mailed statement.  A ceremony at the $1.7 billion Moatize coal mine in
northwestern Tete province will include Mozambican President
Armando Guebuza and Vale Chief Executive Officer  Roger Agnelli ,
the statement said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
